        "title": "Using exceptions with Google Guava",
        "body": "<p>What is the best pattern for using Google Guava with methods that should throw exceptions?<\/p>\n\n<p>Let's say I have:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public Sting someMethod(Integer i) throws SomeException;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>And I want to do:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; s=Lists.transform(is,new Function&lt;String, Integer&gt;() {\n       public String apply(Integer i) {\n         return someMethod(i);\n       }\n     });\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I couldn't do the above because of the exception.  Is there any nice pattern for handling it?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 25005112,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "exception",
            "guava"
        ],
        "score": 9,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 5630,
